This paper discusses the security protocols in Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs), which falls under the category of computer networks and security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the link layer security framework, which is a subfield of network security (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm is based on Bloom filters, which are commonly used in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves analyzing and comparing different approaches, which can be considered as a form of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm, which can be categorized as software engineering (cs.SE).
